annotationA: Cell division control protein; Cdc6 is an essential component of the pre-Replication complex (preRC) together with the origin recognition complex, dup and MCM2-7 proteins. The preRC is present at all chromosomal origins of replication and is required for the initiation of DNA replication. Cdc6 also functions in the co-ordination of DNA replication with mitosis, and may contribute to apoptosis and transcription
annotationB: Ovarian-specific serine/threonine-protein kinase Lok; May have a role in germline establishment; Belongs to the protein kinase superfamily. CAMK Ser/Thr protein kinase family. CDS1 subfamily
